body_text.text:
Sera positive for rabies virus from dogs immunized with various rabies vaccines were tested by ICTS with 3 different operators. When the virus neutralizing antibody titer of the serum samples was ≥0.5 IU/ml as determined by FAVN tests, the results by ICTS were all positive. The results were negative by ICTS when the serum samples were negative or with a titer < 0.5 IU/ml (Table 1
). The sensitivity of the ICTS was also demonstrated by testing 152 selected serum samples with titers ranging from 0.2 IU/ml to 0.8 IU/ml as determined by FAVN tests (Table 2
). Results showed that of the 108 sera with titers ≥ 0.5 IU/ml, 100 (92.6%) produced a distinct band on the test line, and 8 (7.4%) gave a negative response. Of the 8 sera giving a negative result, all of them had VNA titer ranging from 0.5 IU/ml to 0.7 IU/ml.
